race.comment: NAMBROK NICK (3) has a strong record this journey here with three wins and a minor from seven starts. Placed last time (23.04) at Warragul in a Grade 5, finishing third and beaten 4 lengths. Rates on top and should go close. ORANGE RATIO (8) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 2.25 lengths at Geelong in a handy 22.70 beating My Boy Parker. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from five starts. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. REDGUM WARS (4) wasn't far away at the finish when 5th and beaten only 2 lengths (19.76) at this track. Form here at the trip sound including nine wins. Should be thereabouts. FAST LEGS (7) was unplaced here last start but gets her chance to atone.
